Three suspects from Emalahleni Municipality have been arrested for fraud and money laundering to the value of R1.6 million. They are a Member of Mayoral Committee (MMC) aged 49 a former ward councillor 44 and a member of a co-operative 39. It is alleged that in 2013 the suspects embezzled money from a co-operative. It is further alleged that farmers were hiring the farms from the co-operative and the suspects took the money for themselves police said.The three suspects will be appearing in court today in Witbank. A fourth suspect is being sought.